    <text>
        <body>
            
            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.19.8-9_0001"/>
                
                <note type="curatorial">Missouri Collection</note>
                <fw type="curatorial">8</fw>
                
                <fw type="letterhead">
                    <hi rend="caps">OLIVER K. BOVARD
                        <lb/>
                    CONWAY AND BALLAS ROADS
                        <lb/>
                    CLAYTON, MISSOURI</hi>
                </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>Aug 1/41</dateline>
                
                    <salute>Dear Neihardt- .</salute>
                </opener>
                <p>Congratulations on the completion of your long work. However engrosed you may have been, you must have had a <unclear>yen</unclear> for the day that <unclear>come</unclear> at last. Did you <hi rend="underline">jump</hi> up and shout "Whoops!" or just roll a cigarette?</p>
                
                <p>I shall be only too happy to tell Mellett that you will prove a "good <unclear/> anywhere you put him" as Van Walton, friend of Clark McAdams and <unclear>caretaker</unclear> and terror of Cuivre Island <unclear>panted</unclear> when Mac pinned him in an impromptu wrestling bout + Mellett has stuff himself and I am sure you would find association with him agreeable. I agree in
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4a.19.8-9_0002"/>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">9</fw>
                    <fw type="authorial">2</fw>
                
                    in principal with your observations in the State of Man. I think all the major trends are in the right direction. And what a lot of good laughs on the front page! Harry Hopkins the anti-Socialist social <unclear>maker</unclear>, presenting the felicitation of his boss the "Savior of Capitalism" to the hotel Bolsheviks, the latest.</p> 
                
                <p>Best wishes in all things. <del/>I am in splendid health, thank you, working on the farm every day. I trust you too are storing up energy for the great <del/> times which are to come</p>
                <closer>
                    <salute>Faithfully yours</salute>
                    <signed>OK Bovard</signed>
                </closer>
                
            </div1>
        </body>
        
